The paper deals with matrix completion, a problem that is commonly studied in machine learning and data science. The proposed algorithm involves active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that focuses on selecting informative samples to label or query. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which are relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with real-world applications, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
